&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Introduction:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you searching for an opportunity to play a key role in driving the dramatic growth of a highly successful software company?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Poppulo, we’re working on what’s next in communications and workplace technology. As a pioneer in this industry, we understand that meaningfully reaching every employee is hard. And so is managing office space in a hybrid world. And so is improving the customer and guest experience. We exist to make each of these things easier. We exist to bring harmony to our customers. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And we do that at enterprise scale. Our omnichannel employee communications, customer communications, and workplace experience platform is trusted by over 6,000 organizations today, reaching more than 35M employees and delivering content to 500,000+ digital signs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We know there’s no such thing as a “perfect&quot; candidate - we’re all a work in progress and are growing new skills and capabilities all the time. We encourage you to apply for a position with Poppulo even if you don’t meet 100% of the requirements. We believe in fostering an environment where there is a diversity of perspectives, in hopes that we can all thrive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Business Development Representative (BDR) will be responsible for inbound and outbound sales prospecting, initiating the follow-up and first outreach with potential customers.&amp;nbsp; Inbound sales activities will take precedence over outbound in this specific role. They will conduct cold calls, follow up via email using Sales Enablement technology and using social selling to help book meetings. BDR’s will also take the first high-level exploratory call with prospects and pass qualified opportunities to the Enterprise Sales team using BANT methodology. They will be responsible for expanding our customer base by using prospecting strategies and technology to identify new opportunities. Business Development Representative’s will work closely with Account Executives and enjoy working with cross functional teams, especially Marketing, Sales Operations and Product. They will report to the Business Development Manager. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of our buyer personas and the needs/pains of our target market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct cold calls and cold emails to prospects across multiple departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate and qualify opportunities using the BANT methodology to hand over to Sales Representatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and adapt call and email scripts and outreach sequences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize social selling techniques to attract and source leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update and maintain detailed notes in our CRM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the team to brainstorm and execute new strategies to attract our target market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on industry trends, news, competitors, and our target market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore and utilize various prospecting tools and software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in networking activities, face-to-face meetings, and other lead generation activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills/Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 1+ year of experience in an inbound or outbound-focused Business Development Representative role, Sales Account Executive, or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience and comfort with cold-selling via email and telephone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent research skills and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in reaching monthly and quarterly targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;P

